claim.claim-text:
An object information acquisition apparatus according to claim 6, further comprising:
a light source configured to emit light;
wherein the capacitive transducer is configured to receive an acoustic wave generated by the light that has been emitted from the light source to irradiate an object, and the signal processor is configured to process a signal obtained by conversion into an electric signal, to thereby acquire information on the object.

A method of manufacturing the capacitive transducer according to any one of claims 1 to 5, the method comprising:
forming a first electrode of multiple kinds of the cells;
forming a sacrificial layer on the first electrode in order to form a gap of each of the multiple kinds of the cells;
forming, on the sacrificial layer, at least a part of a vibrating film of the each of the multiple kinds of the cells; and
removing the sacrificial layer,
wherein the forming a sacrificial layer and the forming at least a part of a vibrating film comprise setting different ratios of an area of the second electrode of the each of the multiple kinds of cells to an area of the sacrificial layer that forms the gap of the each of the multiple kinds of cells.
